{
  "text": "Pringle et al. [CITATION_1] reported higher VO 2Max values in horizontal and uphill maximum progressive protocols (3.84 \u00b1 0.57 L/min [0% slope] and 3.95 \u00b1 0.60 L/min [10% slope], pattern in the frequency ratio of past metabolic cost, suggesting mechanical inefficiency at low pass frequencies, and higher cost associated with the production of force at high pass frequencies, hence a worsening which is ultimately detrimental to economy.",
